# Agent todo workflow

Use the todo list tool for **multi-step** work only; skip it for single obvious edits or Q&A.

## Use todos when

- More than one meaningful step (e.g. investigate → change → verify → commit).
- Order matters or work spans several files or systems.
- Risk of losing track (git + tests + push, migrations, etc.).

## Keep lists lean

- Few items; outcome-shaped titles (e.g. “Run build and fix failures”), not micro-tasks.
- At most one item `in_progress`; mark completed as you go; cancel if scope changes.

## Do not require todos for

- One small, localized change with a clear end state.
- Explanations or planning with no repo edits.
